OL,3,CGuernsey doctors told to phase out
OL,4,Cpain relief plasters
OL,6,FTeena Bhogal, Chief Pharmacist, said:
OL,7,F"The evidence supporting the use of
OL,8,Flidocaine plasters for nerve pain is
OL,9,Flimited and they are relatively
OL,10,Fexpensive compared to other pain
OL,11,Ftreatments, making them less cost-
OL,12,Feffective."
OL,14,FCurrently, the National Institute for
OL,15,FHealth and Care Excellence (NICE) does
OL,16,Fnot recommend lidocaine plasters for
OL,17,Fnerve pain due to "insufficient
OL,18,Fevidence".
